Name: The Sting-Rays

text: The Sting-Rays (often credited The Stingrays) were a British Garage Rock and Psychobilly band from Greater London which recorded on Ace Records' garage and psychedelic subsidiary Big Beat and Joe Foster's Kaleidoscope Sound in the 1980s.[1][2][3][4][5][6]
Most of the band's songs were written by Alec Palao and Bal Croce
